<br>
I rolled a hammer troll skald a month ago when I got back into DAoC and I basically went with hammer because IMHO a Troll should use hammer. I did not use any maths etc to make that decision and actually uberness was never a consideration, then I would not have rolled a skald in the first place. I pull aggro of yellow/orange-con Thanes/Savages 90% of the time with Provoke. So I am quite happy with my skald.<br>
<br>
I am willing to enhance my learning curve and I follow some of the arguments here why you should go axe. If someone could actually give some numbers/estimate how much his damage output has increased since  switching to axe.<br>
<br>
I should add that I have decent equipment, using a WoW drop 2H Legendary Ice Breaker with 35% bonus. I could probably get equivalent 2H axes if I would respec.<br>
<br>
Edited in: I went to spredsheets and compared growth rates of rear positional styles axe vs hammer:<br>
<br>
1. Evern + Arc Rift: 0.62+0.98 = 1.60<br>
2. Conq + Sledgeh: 0.74+0.94 = 1.68<br>
<br>
Sorry but I see no difference here, in fron styles axe is clearly superior with Havoc/Tyrs Fury @50 axe.<br>
