<br>
I think Hammer wins if you need to conserve End usage (provoke's low End usage seems like a data bug never corrected).<br>
<br>
I think Hammer wins if you want to concentrate on runners and rear positionals.  Conquer snares!  No more runners!  To get a snare with an axe you will need to land Pillager then Plunder (and ignore Evernight/Arctic Rift).<br>
<br>
Hammer seems to win if you want effects like snare and stun.  Hammer has a stun off an anytime style, while axe requires a parry to stun.<br>
<br>
Axe seems to have the highest straight up fighting damage though.  While you are mashing the 0.58 Provoke, Axe users are probably mashing Havoc/Tyr's for 0.75 then 0.94.  If axe users can't get Havoc to land, we are losing a lot of damage and Hammer looks better because Provoke uses less End than Plague.<br>
<br>
Finally, I think most of our enemies take more damage from the axe slashing weapon than the hammer crush weapon, if you look at the armor resist charts?<br>
<br>
-Leitari, MLF <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gotterdaoc>GotterDAOC</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/23/03 12:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=535.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://unforsakensouls.us/mask_square.png WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hammer all the way</span><hr size=1> A total revamp of all style lines is in the design phase right now, so I'd hold off on making any decision on weapons based on style line.<br>
<br>
If the damage bonuses don't change, then you should take into account that Albion is neutral to slash for all armor types, and Hibernia scale is vulnerable to slash while Hibernia reinforced is vulnerable to crush. That seems to indicate that slash is the win over all in terms of bonus damage (unless you're a bard killing specialist).<br>
